[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ill sailor airlifted from yacht off Llandudno's Great Orme

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A sailor has been airlifted to hospital after falling ill on his yacht off the north Wales coast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Llandudno RNLI lifeboat was called to the vessel 6 miles (10km) off the Great Orme, Conwy county at 09:00 BST on Friday.
By 09.50 BST the man had been winched into a coastguard rescue helicopter and was flown to hospital in Bangor.
